      "lesson title": "Over-Automation in Customer Service",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores the growing trend of automation in customer service and examines the point at which it begins to harm rather than help the guest experience. You will learn to recognise the warning signs of over-automation, including frustrated customers, unresolved complaints, and declining satisfaction scores. We will look at real-world examples where businesses have replaced too much human interaction with chatbots, automated responses, and self-service systems, and consider what went wrong. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to strike the right balance between efficient automation and the genuine human connection that guests often need. This is a practical, beginner-friendly introduction designed to help you make smarter decisions about where automation supports your team and where it gets in the way.",
