          "subtitle": "Blending Technology With a Human Touch",
          "slidecontent": "• Automating routine tasks (like booking confirmations) while keeping humans available for complaints and complex queries\n• A simple \"speak to a person\" option goes a long way\n• Mapping the customer journey to identify which touchpoints genuinely benefit from automation and which require empathy\n• Monitoring satisfaction scores after any new automation is introduced\n• Training staff to step in smoothly when technology falls short\n• Treating automation as a support tool, not a replacement for genuine service"
